# Module: `packages/common`

- Shared utilities only — no UI rendering, no canvas, no element mutation logic
- Allowed cross-package imports:
  - `@excalidraw/math` — value and type imports permitted
  - `@excalidraw/element/types` — **type-only** imports permitted
  - `@excalidraw/excalidraw/types` — **type-only** imports permitted
- All other upward imports are forbidden (e.g. importing from `packages/excalidraw` internals beyond `/types`)
- No circular imports — `@excalidraw/common` must not be imported back into `@excalidraw/math`

## How to verify

```bash
# Value imports from element or excalidraw (not type-only) should return nothing:
grep -r "^import {" packages/common/src/ | grep -E "@excalidraw/(element|excalidraw)" | grep -v "import type"

# Imports from packages other than math/element/excalidraw should return nothing:
grep -r "@excalidraw/" packages/common/src/ | grep -v "@excalidraw/(math|element/types|excalidraw/types)"

# Build must succeed with no circular-dependency errors:
yarn build:packages
```